1. SQLite database (items.db)

This is just a file created in your project folder.
It stores your data permanently (unlike Python dicts).

2. SQLAlchemy ORM (Object Relational Mapper)

Converts Python classes ↔ SQL tables.
You define a class (ItemDB) → SQLAlchemy creates a corresponding items table in SQLite.

3. FastAPI app

Exposes HTTP endpoints.
When you call /buckets/... endpoints, FastAPI uses SQLAlchemy to interact with the SQLite database.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

demo3/
│── demo3.py        # your FastAPI app
│── database.py     # SQLAlchemy + SQLite setup
│── items.db        # (auto-created SQLite DB file)


-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


